            "type": "text",
            "title": "Default Title",
            "metadata": "",
            "content": "Amir H. Davarpanah, MD • Linton W. Eberhardt, MD<|txt_split|>From the Department of Radiology and Imaging Sciences, Emory University School of Medicine, Emory University Hospital, 1364 Clifton Rd NE, Atlanta, GA 30322. Received February 25, 2019; revision requested April 5; revision received April 22; accepted April 24. Adhere ascorrepond to AHTD (e-mail: aadanspae@emory.edu).<|txt_split|>Conflicts of interest are listed at the end of this article.<|txt_split|>Radiology 2020,295:733-735 \\(\\clubsuit\\) https://doi.org/10.1148/radiol.2020190435 \\(\\clubsuit\\) Content code:GI \\(\\clubsuit\\) RSNA, 2020<|txt_split|>Mistry A 63-year-old woman with a history of left mastectomy for breast cancer and partial gastrectomy with Roux-en-Y reconstruction for nonhealing peptic ulcer presented to the emergency department and reported a 1-month history of abdominal distention; she was on a high dose of metronidazole, but had no previous history of abdominal pain. She was on a high dose of metronidazole, but she had continued fever, diarrhea, abdominal bloating, and loss of appetite. She reported no contact with a sick person or recent travel. At admission, laboratory studies revealed leukocytosis, with a white blood cell count of \\(15.1 \\times 10^{9} / \\mu \\mathrm{L}\\) \\((15.1 \\times 10^{9} / \\mu \\mathrm{L})\\) (normal range, \\(0.48 - 1.27 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\)) and a low serum creatinine level of \\(1.5 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\) (normal range, \\(0.48 - 1.27 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\)). The patient was on a high dose of metronidazole, but she had no previous history of abdominal pain, and a C-reactive protein level of \\(203.8 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\) \\((194.0 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL})\\) \\((194.0 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL})\\) (normal range, \\(\\leq 10 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\) \\((\\geq 59.2 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL})\\). Liver enzyme levels were elevated, with an alanine aminotransferase of 48 U/L \\((0.80 \\mu \\mathrm{kU} / \\mathrm{L})\\) (normal range, \\(0 - 29 \\mathrm{U} / \\mathrm{L}\\) \\((0 - 0.48 \\mu \\mathrm{kU} / \\mathrm{L})\\), an apatase aminotransferase of \\(98 \\mathrm{U} / \\mathrm{L}\\) \\((1.6 \\mu \\mathrm{kU} / \\mathrm{L})\\) (normal range, \\(0 - 39 \\mathrm{U} / \\mathrm{L}\\) \\((0.16 - 0.62 \\mu \\mathrm{kU} / \\mathrm{L})\\), an alkaline phosphatase level of \\(1.5 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\) (normal range, \\(0 - 3.5 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\)), and a total bilirubin level of \\(1.5 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\) \\((25.7 \\mu \\mathrm{mol} / \\mathrm{dL}\\), normal range, \\(0 - 3.3 \\mathrm{mg} / \\mathrm{dL}\\) \\((1.5 - 1.71 \\mu \\mathrm{mol} / \\mathrm{dL})\\). Adenobiprolenic CT showed Fig. 1 (3).",
